      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Allow WhatsApp WebSocket URL override",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nThe WhatsApp plugin had no minimal way to point the real Baileys client at an alternate WhatsApp Web-compatible socket endpoint.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThis adds a generic `OPENCLAW_WHATSAPP_WEB_SOCKET_URL` env override in the WhatsApp session creation path. When set, it is validated as `ws://` or `wss://` and passed through to Baileys as `waWebSocketUrl`; when unset, normal production behavior continues to use Baileys defaults.\n\nRelated Crabline PR: https://github.com/openclaw/crabline/pull/23\n\n## User Impact\n\nProduction users see no behavior change by default. QA and local test infrastructure can point WhatsApp at a mock socket server without adding Crabline-specific imports, config schema, fixture plumbing, or alternate socket factories to the WhatsApp plugin.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/whatsapp/src/session.test.ts`\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check extensions/whatsapp/src/session.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/session.test.ts`\n- `pnpm exec oxlint --deny-warnings --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.extensions.json extensions/whatsapp/src/session.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/session.test.ts`\n- `pnpm tsgo:extensions:test`\n",
